1
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
"Double Helix"

2
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:18,000
Not sentimental in the least.

3
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,359
A truly masterful touch.

4
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:22,599
The more the audience suffers,

5
00:01:23,519 --> 00:01:25,079
the colder the camera becomes.

6
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,000
True suffering...

7
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,799
is something you can't even put into words.

8
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:38,959
For example,

9
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,000
this weather.

10
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,920
Looks like we'll be stuck here for a while.

11
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,120
Got anything to eat?

12
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:51,959
I'm starving.

13
00:01:54,439 --> 00:01:55,439
Instant noodles.

14
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:57,959
Is that okay?

15
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,519
Sure.

16
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:23,199
Oh, shoot.

17
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,600
I don't think there are any bowls.

18
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,480
We can just eat out of the pot.

19
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:45,759
This looks pretty good.

20
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,280
I'm digging in, then.

21
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,360
Give me the spoon.

22
00:03:40,039 --> 00:03:42,240
How am I supposed to drink
the soup without a spoon?

23
00:04:01,599 --> 00:04:02,599
This is delicious.

24
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,080
To make instant noodles taste this good...

25
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:05,919
it's really something.

26
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,159
Xiao Chen.

27
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,295
If you could make noodles
for me for the rest of my life,

28
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,319
that would be perfect.

29
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,159
It's just instant noodles.

30
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:17,240
You can't eat this
every day for a lifetime.

31
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,079
In the future,

32
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:22,000
someone else will make you better food.

33
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,160
This rain...

34
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,600
I wonder when it's going to stop.

35
00:04:32,519 --> 00:04:34,000
If you don't mind,

36
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:36,319
could I stay the night?

37
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:43,500
(Episode 4: What the hell did you do to my brother?)

38
00:04:49,119 --> 00:04:51,400
Don't you have any other pajamas?

39
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,480
This is the only set.

40
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,319
Well...

41
00:04:58,639 --> 00:04:59,439
you should get some rest.

42
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,240
I'm going to sleep in the small room.

43
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,480
Think about it.

44
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:18,560
Break up with your girlfriend

45
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,000
and get back together with me.

46
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:32,279
What's wrong?

47
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,160
The AC is broken.

48
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,480
No, it's not.

49
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,800
It's working.

50
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,399
You lied to me.

51
00:06:15,279 --> 00:06:16,879
You don't even have a girlfriend.

52
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,240
You still care about me,

53
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:25,639
don't you?

54
00:06:29,519 --> 00:06:30,519
No.

55
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,920
You're lying.

56
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,199
You haven't forgotten me.

57
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,560
I miss you.

58
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,319
I really, really miss you.

59
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:32,759
Xiao Chen.

60
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,720
Let's get back together.

61
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,360
Okay?

62
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,040
No.

63
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,560
You're still lying to me.

64
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:18,199
A long time ago,

65
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:20,639
you said the same thing to me.

66
00:08:22,079 --> 00:08:23,879
So, can I assume

67
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,040
that you also

68
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,319
still love me?

69
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:53,999
I'm heading back to the office.

70
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,120
I'll give you the day off.

71
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,320
Move in with me.

72
00:08:57,679 --> 00:08:59,480
The code is 251010.

73
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:21,840
Son.

74
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,559
Is everything okay over there?

75
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:25,559
Everything's great, Mom.

76
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:27,239
My colleagues are all really nice.

77
00:09:27,559 --> 00:09:28,600
They're all young.

78
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,000
And the company benefits are good, too.

79
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,159
If it works out,

80
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,279
I wouldn't mind working here

81
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,480
until I retire.

82
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,159
Are there a lot of girls at the company?

83
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,200
It's alright.

84
00:09:41,679 --> 00:09:42,879
Well, keep an eye out.

85
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,600
If you meet a nice, suitable girl,

86
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:45,759
make a move.

87
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,359
Settle down and start a family soon.

88
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,399
It would put my mind at ease.

89
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:51,879
Mom, I have to go.

90
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,599
I still need to unpack at my new place.

91
00:09:53,799 --> 00:09:55,320
Okay, go on then.

92
00:10:29,399 --> 00:10:30,399
Chou Cheng.

93
00:10:30,739 --> 00:10:32,419
Get me Zhu Sha from the design department.

94
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,840
Okay.

95
00:10:37,068 --> 00:10:38,761
[The convo he had with
Yichen, sent 7 days ago]

96
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:52,919
Yichen.

97
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,920
You look like you've lost weight recently.

98
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,399
You were already thin,

99
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:58,399
but now your clothes
are just hanging off you.

100
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,559
Is something wrong?

101
00:11:01,039 --> 00:11:02,879
No, I'm just tired from work.

102
00:11:04,519 --> 00:11:05,159
Let me treat you to a good meal.

103
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:05,799
My treat.

104
00:11:05,879 --> 00:11:06,879
- How about it?
- No, no.

105
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Let's go, let's go.

106
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,200
Come on.

107
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:10,519
Let's go.

108
00:11:12,279 --> 00:11:13,799
How about we get some sukiyaki later?

109
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,639
Sounds good.

110
00:11:14,759 --> 00:11:16,320
The fresh shrimp there is amazing.

111
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,799
I think later,

112
00:11:17,879 --> 00:11:19,015
I'm going to get an extra order of udon.

113
00:11:19,039 --> 00:11:20,039
What do you think?

114
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,840
You guys take your time. I have to go.

115
00:11:24,639 --> 00:11:25,279
What are you doing?

116
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,559
Why didn't you text me back?

117
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,320
I haven't made up my mind yet.

118
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:41,320
Is it because you don't want to be with me?

119
00:11:41,559 --> 00:11:42,559
No.

120
00:11:42,679 --> 00:11:43,720
Don't push me.

121
00:11:44,519 --> 00:11:46,200
So, do you want to start over or not?

122
00:11:46,559 --> 00:11:47,600
I don't know.

123
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:49,599
Can you just give me
some more time to think?

124
00:11:49,679 --> 00:11:50,879
What is there to think about?

125
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:53,600
Yes or no?

126
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,560
Is it really that hard to answer?

127
00:12:05,799 --> 00:12:06,799
Fine.

128
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,799
I'll give you some more time.

129
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,640
When you've made up your mind,

130
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,320
come find me.

131
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:25,799
It's not that I don't want to.

132
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,559
I'm just scared.

133
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:32,559
What if I take this step and fall again?

134
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:36,480
I'm afraid I won't be able to get back up.

135
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,799
Okay, I get it.

136
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,475
[Same conversation, no updates]

137
00:13:18,159 --> 00:13:19,320
You two haven't made up yet?

138
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:20,919
No.

139
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
We're just old classmates.

140
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,960
Who are you kidding?

141
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,960
It's obvious there's
something between you two.

142
00:13:29,152 --> 00:13:29,833
What?

143
00:13:30,279 --> 00:13:32,080
Afraid we'll use you to get connections?

144
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,520
What are you talking about?

145
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,200
I'm going to the restroom.

146
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:41,720
Ding-ding.

147
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,440
If you two get together,

148
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:46,039
don't you dare fly off
into the sunset together

149
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:47,720
and leave me all alone.

150
00:13:47,799 --> 00:13:48,799
Don't worry.

151
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:51,519
By the way, Yichen.

152
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:54,159
How come I've never seen you date anyone?

153
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,840
Me?

154
00:13:57,919 --> 00:13:58,919
I'm afraid of heartbreak.

155
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,760
You're also afraid of car accidents,

156
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:03,456
but you still ride in cars every day.

157
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,480
That's different.

158
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,720
A car accident is over in an instant.

159
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:08,560
But being abandoned by someone...

160
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,399
that's a terrible feeling.

161
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,240
You always seem so carefree.

162
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,240
I never thought you'd be so timid.

163
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,679
If I were as indecisive as you,

164
00:14:17,919 --> 00:14:19,440
I wouldn't even be able to get close

165
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:20,519
to Zhu Sha.

166
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,559
Opportunity

167
00:14:21,799 --> 00:14:23,000
is for those who are prepared.

168
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,720
And happiness

169
00:14:25,279 --> 00:14:26,639
is only for the brave.

170
00:14:30,998 --> 00:14:31,998
Ding-ding.

171
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,240
I have a question for you.

172
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:36,480
What if...

173
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,679
your ex

174
00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:40,416
came back and wanted to get back together?

175
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,440
Would you say yes?

176
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,480
Do you love them?

177
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,400
Then that's all that matters.

178
00:14:48,759 --> 00:14:49,960
What's the big deal?

179
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,000
If you both love each other,

180
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,000
why wouldn't you accept?

181
00:14:56,799 --> 00:14:58,399
But there was a time

182
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,255
when they didn't love me anymore.

183
00:15:00,279 --> 00:15:01,279
You're hung up on that?

184
00:15:01,639 --> 00:15:03,720
So you're just mad about it.

185
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,440
No.

186
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:08,159
I'm afraid of being abandoned again.

187
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,559
They came back this time,

188
00:15:09,879 --> 00:15:11,079
but they didn't explain anything

189
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,200
or apologize.

190
00:15:12,399 --> 00:15:14,039
They just said we should get back together.

191
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,800
It's not that I don't want to.

192
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,840
I'm just scared.

193
00:15:18,759 --> 00:15:20,200
I don't get your logic.

194
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,799
This is a simple thing,

195
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,720
so why are you making it so complicated?

196
00:15:23,759 --> 00:15:24,439
You love each other.

197
00:15:24,679 --> 00:15:25,720
Just be together.

198
00:15:25,919 --> 00:15:28,399
At least give yourself and them a chance.

199
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,760
Who knows what will happen in the future?

200
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,120
This fried noodle place is amazing.

201
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,200
Thanks, Cheng Yichen.

202
00:15:56,919 --> 00:15:58,039
Our bet is still on.

203
00:15:58,159 --> 00:15:59,936
When you score in the
top 15 on the next test,

204
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,200
it'll be our turn to treat you.

205
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,240
We'll see.

206
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,080
How could there be such a big difference?

207
00:16:11,559 --> 00:16:12,559
See?

208
00:16:13,399 --> 00:16:14,399
Cheng Yichen.

209
00:16:18,279 --> 00:16:19,439
I have something to show you.

210
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,039
Look, it's brand new.

211
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,640
A reward for getting into the top fifteen.

212
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:26,399
My dad gave it to me.

213
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:27,639
Come on.

214
00:16:27,879 --> 00:16:29,599
Let's check out the sound quality together.

215
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:37,559
Like this.

216
00:16:37,679 --> 00:16:38,919
Close your eyes.

217
00:17:02,159 --> 00:17:03,159
Lu Feng.

218
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,640
Come on, lets go play soccer.

219
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,880
I'm going to play soccer first.

220
00:17:07,519 --> 00:17:08,559
You can borrow it for now.

221
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,240
All my fried noodles combined...

222
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,295
wouldn't even cover
the cost of the cable.

223
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,319
Oh, you.

224
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,240
You made me lose the bet.

225
00:17:25,039 --> 00:17:26,519
Now I don't even have money for food.

226
00:18:34,599 --> 00:18:36,079
Your score was calculated wrong.

227
00:18:37,039 --> 00:18:39,319
If you add the points they missed...

228
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,680
you should be first in the entire grade.

229
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:45,880
You...

230
00:18:47,119 --> 00:18:48,599
are you worried about...

231
00:18:49,319 --> 00:18:50,319
this?

232
00:18:55,206 --> 00:18:56,966
I can get good grades on my own merit.

233
00:18:57,078 --> 00:18:58,199
I don't need your charity.

234
00:19:01,799 --> 00:19:04,240
Don't assume everyone
is as scheming as you are.

235
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,240
I just thought this player was cool.

236
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:08,206
I didn't mean anything else by it.

237
00:19:08,478 --> 00:19:10,119
It'd be a shame if it went to waste.

238
00:19:10,346 --> 00:19:12,279
But whether you want it or not...
that's your business.

239
00:19:12,319 --> 00:19:13,599
What does it have to do with me?

240
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,240
I don't like being indebted to people.

241
00:19:18,559 --> 00:19:19,559
How about this?

242
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,319
I'll treat you to a meal.

243
00:19:22,839 --> 00:19:23,839
No.

244
00:19:30,039 --> 00:19:31,039
Fine.

245
00:19:43,039 --> 00:19:44,640
Hello sir, here's your steak.

246
00:19:53,039 --> 00:19:54,039
Please enjoy.

247
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,440
Thanks.

248
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:28,799
Waiter.

249
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,240
Can I get a pair of chopsticks?

250
00:20:30,559 --> 00:20:31,799
Waiter, never mind.

251
00:20:33,079 --> 00:20:34,079
Silly.

252
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,480
They don't have chopsticks here.

253
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:54,880
So?

254
00:20:55,079 --> 00:20:56,079
Is it good?

255
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,045
You can eat it like that?

256
00:20:58,472 --> 00:21:00,312
I was just going to
bite into the whole thing.

257
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,240
Cheng Yichen.

258
00:21:20,319 --> 00:21:21,319
Happy graduation.

259
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,160
Happy graduation.

260
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:49,559
What Ding-ding said...

261
00:21:50,279 --> 00:21:51,720
wasn't enough to convince me.

262
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,000
But, Lu Feng...

263
00:21:55,559 --> 00:21:57,079
I want to take a gamble one more time.

264
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:01,160
I'm betting all the courage
and luck I have left.

265
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:08,920
Can we still be happy,
after I've gone all in like this?

266
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,480
Hey handsome, you've got a visitor.

267
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:24,720
Who is it?

268
00:23:28,559 --> 00:23:29,559
Xiao Chen.

269
00:23:31,839 --> 00:23:32,839
Xiao Chen.

270
00:23:33,559 --> 00:23:35,000
Xiao Chen, let me explain.

271
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,559
It's not what you think.

272
00:23:36,759 --> 00:23:37,759
Xiao Chen.

273
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:38,880
Xiao Chen.

274
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,000
Listen to me.

275
00:23:40,079 --> 00:23:41,479
It's absolutely not what you think.

276
00:23:41,504 --> 00:23:42,625
- Xiao Chen...
- Don't bother.

277
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:44,840
If you need someone to sleep with...

278
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,840
I'm clearly not the right person.

279
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:26,480
Hey handsome, all alone?

280
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,160
Who are you?

281
00:24:37,359 --> 00:24:38,359
Xiao Chen.

282
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,160
Take me home, okay?

283
00:24:43,559 --> 00:24:44,559
Sure.

284
00:25:24,039 --> 00:25:24,720
What is it?

285
00:25:24,759 --> 00:25:25,319
Mr. Lu.

286
00:25:25,359 --> 00:25:27,015
The personnel changes need your signature.

287
00:25:27,039 --> 00:25:28,399
When are you coming to the office?

288
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:29,799
Who's resigning?

289
00:25:30,119 --> 00:25:31,119
Cheng Yichen.

290
00:25:32,559 --> 00:25:33,936
Tell him to wait for me in my office.

291
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:34,960
I'll be there soon.

292
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:41,720
No!

293
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:42,920
Xiao Chen.

294
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Xiao Chen.

295
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,720
Mr. Lu.

296
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,640
I've already spoken with
Special Assistant Chou.

297
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:02,160
I just need you to sign this, please.

298
00:26:13,799 --> 00:26:14,799
Xiao Chen.

299
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,560
What happened last night
was a misunderstanding.

300
00:26:17,599 --> 00:26:19,136
You don't have to explain anything to me.

301
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,400
I'm just here to resign.

302
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,640
Xiao Chen.

303
00:26:28,039 --> 00:26:29,039
I admit...

304
00:26:29,279 --> 00:26:31,416
I was wrong to bring
someone home when I was drunk.

305
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:32,799
But I didn't do anything.

306
00:26:33,559 --> 00:26:34,279
Before you came in...

307
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,000
I was already about to ask him to leave.

308
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:37,720
Believe me.

309
00:26:38,786 --> 00:26:40,026
It's not that it didn't happen.

310
00:26:40,365 --> 00:26:42,085
It's that you didn't get the chance, right?

311
00:26:42,599 --> 00:26:43,599
That's not it.

312
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,480
I could never touch anyone else.

313
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:46,960
I swear to you.

314
00:26:47,119 --> 00:26:48,759
From now on, no matter how drunk I get...

315
00:26:49,119 --> 00:26:50,999
I'll never make such
a stupid mistake again.

316
00:26:52,079 --> 00:26:53,559
Just forgive me this once.

317
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:54,880
Please?

318
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:56,960
Fine.

319
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:58,640
I forgive you.

320
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,079
Don't be angry anymore.

321
00:27:05,039 --> 00:27:06,079
Can you sign this now?

322
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,840
Didn't you just say you forgive me?

323
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:19,560
Then why are you still resigning?

324
00:27:22,279 --> 00:27:23,639
I don't want to work here anymore.

325
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:24,240
Is that a problem?

326
00:27:24,319 --> 00:27:25,319
No.

327
00:27:40,519 --> 00:27:43,000
Breaching the contract unilaterally
requires paying a penalty.

328
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:45,799
Have you seen these figures?

329
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,120
Are you sure you can afford it?

330
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,160
Don't worry.

331
00:27:49,839 --> 00:27:51,079
If I have the guts to resign...

332
00:27:51,599 --> 00:27:52,959
I can definitely afford to pay.

333
00:27:57,599 --> 00:27:59,559
You've really thought of
everything, haven't you?

334
00:28:00,153 --> 00:28:02,393
No, what do you want from me?

335
00:28:02,453 --> 00:28:03,868
Do you want me to get
on my knees and beg you?

336
00:28:04,079 --> 00:28:04,720
No need.

337
00:28:04,905 --> 00:28:06,145
I'm just here to resign.

338
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:13,599
Did I do something so unforgivable?

339
00:28:14,352 --> 00:28:15,793
I didn't even touch him.

340
00:28:25,580 --> 00:28:26,699
A normal man...

341
00:28:26,813 --> 00:28:28,412
has physical needs.

342
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,319
You're a man.

343
00:28:30,344 --> 00:28:31,624
You know what I'm talking about.

344
00:28:38,039 --> 00:28:39,400
Are you going to tell me...

345
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:41,720
that all these years...

346
00:28:43,079 --> 00:28:44,335
while you were waiting for me...

347
00:28:44,359 --> 00:28:45,720
you really stayed celibate?

348
00:28:57,079 --> 00:28:58,079
What?

349
00:28:58,104 --> 00:28:59,223
I guessed right, didn't I?

350
00:29:00,333 --> 00:29:01,333
Then tell me.

351
00:29:02,359 --> 00:29:04,079
How many have you been with over the years?

352
00:29:04,319 --> 00:29:06,000
Men? Or women?

353
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,640
Did you think...

354
00:29:09,119 --> 00:29:10,999
every single one of
them was better than me?

355
00:29:17,279 --> 00:29:18,640
What's it to you?

356
00:29:20,033 --> 00:29:21,273
Who are you to me?

357
00:29:22,519 --> 00:29:23,799
You don't actually think...

358
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,840
I spent the last four years
foolishly waiting for you, do you?

359
00:29:27,039 --> 00:29:28,039
Unable to forget you?

360
00:29:28,459 --> 00:29:29,499
My heart full of devotion?

361
00:29:30,519 --> 00:29:31,519
Lu Feng.

362
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,799
Don't overthink it.

363
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,320
Every single one of them...

364
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,480
was a thousand, a
million times better than you.

365
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:40,640
Lu Feng.

366
00:29:41,599 --> 00:29:43,160
What do you think you are?

367
00:29:45,559 --> 00:29:46,559
Cheng Yichen!

368
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,160
Lu Feng!

369
00:30:00,319 --> 00:30:02,039
Lu Feng, let go of me!

370
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,640
Let go, you animal!

371
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:04,599
Animal!

372
00:30:04,759 --> 00:30:06,720
Lu Feng, I'll hate you
for the rest of my life!

373
00:30:10,359 --> 00:30:11,480
Suit yourself.

374
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:49,440
What is it?

375
00:30:50,279 --> 00:30:51,480
I can't get away right now.

376
00:30:53,839 --> 00:30:55,519
You can't even handle something like this?

377
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,680
Xiao Chen.

378
00:31:07,079 --> 00:31:08,200
Wait for me here.

379
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,800
I have to take care of something.

380
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,160
I'll be right back.

381
00:31:51,519 --> 00:31:52,519
Xiao Chen.

382
00:32:26,119 --> 00:32:27,119
Xiao Chen.

383
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,799
Xiao Chen, open the door!

384
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,480
Xiao Chen!

385
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,960
Do you know where Cheng Yichen went?

386
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:52,480
Hold on.

387
00:32:53,119 --> 00:32:53,920
I need you to find out right now...

388
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,080
where his brother lives.

389
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,440
Okay.

390
00:33:34,599 --> 00:33:35,599
Bro.

391
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:37,400
Bro.

392
00:33:38,119 --> 00:33:39,160
You're spacing out again.

393
00:33:39,799 --> 00:33:41,119
Is the song I wrote that bad?

394
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:41,920
No.

395
00:33:42,039 --> 00:33:43,039
It's really good.

396
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,800
If it's so good, why are you spacing out?

397
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,240
It's not like it's a funeral dirge.

398
00:33:48,799 --> 00:33:50,400
I'm just a little tired from work.

399
00:33:51,039 --> 00:33:52,039
Tired again?

400
00:33:52,759 --> 00:33:53,759
Bro.

401
00:33:54,759 --> 00:33:56,960
You've been looking really pale lately.

402
00:33:57,279 --> 00:33:59,720
You've been so down ever
since you got back last time.

403
00:34:00,359 --> 00:34:02,199
And you won't tell me
what's wrong when I ask.

404
00:34:03,599 --> 00:34:05,559
Don't tell me you owe
money to some loan sharks.

405
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,360
And you had to run all the way here?

406
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:09,880
If you don't have any money,

407
00:34:10,079 --> 00:34:11,079
I can give you some.

408
00:34:12,039 --> 00:34:13,919
I've been working
part-time and saved up a bit.

409
00:34:14,072 --> 00:34:15,193
If that's still not enough,

410
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:16,640
we can ask Qin Lang for help.

411
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,000
No, that's not it.

412
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:20,320
I'm just really tired.

413
00:34:20,686 --> 00:34:21,249
Really?

414
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,199
Alright, you two.

415
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,360
Time to eat.

416
00:34:28,599 --> 00:34:30,000
Come on, everything's ready.

417
00:34:31,039 --> 00:34:32,639
Why isn't there any spice in this?

418
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:35,175
Weren't you the one with a stomachache
in the middle of the night a few days ago?

419
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:35,960
And you still want spicy food?

420
00:34:36,039 --> 00:34:36,559
Yi-chen.

421
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:37,679
You have a stomachache?

422
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:38,599
In one sitting,

423
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,719
he ate six servings of ice cream.

424
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:41,240
And insisted on extra spicy food.

425
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:42,360
That's enough.

426
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:43,800
Yi-chen.

427
00:34:46,519 --> 00:34:47,679
I can't control you anyway.

428
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,535
I'll have to let your
brother deal with you.

429
00:34:49,559 --> 00:34:50,880
That was just a one-time thing.

430
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:52,239
I'm fine now, Bro.

431
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,896
By the time something
happens, it'll be too late.

432
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:54,639
I get it.

433
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:55,480
Let's eat.

434
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:56,639
Let's eat.

435
00:34:57,639 --> 00:34:58,239
Let's eat.

436
00:34:58,639 --> 00:34:59,320
You guys go ahead and eat.

437
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:00,480
I'm heading to the bar.

438
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:01,079
What's up?

439
00:35:01,119 --> 00:35:01,719
It's nothing.

440
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:04,080
I just need to meet up with
Shen Chao about some work.

441
00:35:04,719 --> 00:35:05,719
Alright.

442
00:35:06,199 --> 00:35:07,319
Should I save you some food?

443
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:08,880
Don't worry about it.

444
00:35:13,939 --> 00:35:15,499
Have you two thought about your future?

445
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,320
Who knows what the future holds?

446
00:35:17,347 --> 00:35:18,522
We'll just take it one step at a time.

447
00:35:18,679 --> 00:35:19,880
Bro, don't just talk about me.

448
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:20,960
Let's eat.

449
00:35:21,199 --> 00:35:22,199
Here.

450
00:35:22,239 --> 00:35:23,239
Eat up.

451
00:35:26,199 --> 00:35:26,800
Open the door.

452
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:27,960
You're back already?

453
00:35:28,159 --> 00:35:29,159
Did you forget your key?

454
00:35:32,199 --> 00:35:33,199
Lu Feng.

455
00:35:33,719 --> 00:35:34,719
Go away.

456
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,840
Get out, get out, get out.

457
00:35:36,119 --> 00:35:37,119
Xiao Chen.

458
00:35:39,719 --> 00:35:40,320
Xiao Chen.

459
00:35:40,599 --> 00:35:41,079
What are you doing?

460
00:35:41,159 --> 00:35:42,159
Xiao Chen.

461
00:35:44,079 --> 00:35:44,880
Was your brother here?

462
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:45,639
No.

463
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:47,000
How did you find my place?

464
00:35:47,719 --> 00:35:49,079
I've looked everywhere.

465
00:35:49,519 --> 00:35:50,519
He has to be here.

466
00:35:50,599 --> 00:35:51,599
Are you crazy?

467
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,320
I'll have you arrested for trespassing.

468
00:35:56,159 --> 00:35:57,159
Where's your brother?

469
00:35:57,239 --> 00:35:58,559
My brother is a grown man.

470
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,480
He can go wherever he wants.

471
00:36:01,519 --> 00:36:02,519
What about you?

472
00:36:02,559 --> 00:36:03,598
You're the one who just up and left.

473
00:36:03,599 --> 00:36:05,519
Weren't you the one who
vanished without a word?

474
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:06,960
So why are you back now?

475
00:36:08,559 --> 00:36:10,055
You think I wanted to leave like that?

476
00:36:10,079 --> 00:36:11,960
My dad forced me to go to the US.

477
00:36:12,199 --> 00:36:13,719
He cut off all contact.

478
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,559
I wrote to your brother.

479
00:36:15,719 --> 00:36:16,880
I wrote so many letters.

480
00:36:17,039 --> 00:36:18,039
He never wrote back.

481
00:36:18,079 --> 00:36:19,319
Don't you dare play the victim.

482
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,718
We never received...

483
00:36:20,719 --> 00:36:22,159
any of your damn letters.

484
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,120
I was afraid he wouldn't get them,

485
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,399
so I sent them to his school.

486
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,400
Not to your house.

487
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,320
Do you think...

488
00:36:27,321 --> 00:36:29,159
you're so clever?

489
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:30,920
After the huge scandal you two caused,

490
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,376
do you think my brother
could've stayed at that school?

491
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:33,559
He had to transfer.

492
00:36:35,599 --> 00:36:36,599
Transfer?

493
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:37,880
Is that an excuse?

494
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,159
He obviously forgot all about me.

495
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:41,558
I wish he really could...

496
00:36:41,559 --> 00:36:42,880
forget all about you.

497
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:45,320
But all these years, he's been like a fool,

498
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,360
waiting for you to come
back with all his heart.

499
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,575
If he hadn't heard that the
great Mr. Lu was getting married,

500
00:36:49,599 --> 00:36:51,079
my brother might have never given up.

501
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,679
Don't make him sound so noble.

502
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,816
If he was really waiting
for me with all his heart,

503
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:57,976
why were there so many other men?

504
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,256
- Too many to count.
- What are you talking about?

505
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:00,760
Who's been feeding you that nonsense?

506
00:37:01,599 --> 00:37:03,239
Xiao Chen told me himself.

507
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,239
You must have done something...

508
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,360
to hurt my brother.

509
00:37:07,719 --> 00:37:08,880
He said that on purpose.

510
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:10,960
I get it now.

511
00:37:11,119 --> 00:37:12,416
It's because you were getting married.

512
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:13,880
That's why my brother said that.

513
00:37:17,119 --> 00:37:18,400
I'm not getting married.

514
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,159
Xiao Chen knows that.

515
00:37:20,239 --> 00:37:21,920
Then you must have done something else.

516
00:37:23,559 --> 00:37:25,119
He caught you in bed with someone else?

517
00:37:29,599 --> 00:37:30,599
You bastard.

518
00:37:33,119 --> 00:37:34,400
I just had too much to drink.

519
00:37:34,599 --> 00:37:35,816
I mistook someone else for Xiao Chen.

520
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:36,639
Nothing happened.

521
00:37:36,719 --> 00:37:37,440
He's the only one I want.

522
00:37:37,441 --> 00:37:38,639
To hell with you!

523
00:37:40,239 --> 00:37:41,999
Do you have any idea how much
courage it took for my brother...

524
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,320
to come looking for you?

525
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,080
Are you trying to drive him to his grave?

526
00:37:47,519 --> 00:37:48,519
I admit it.

527
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:49,800
It was my fault.

528
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:50,639
But if I was wrong,

529
00:37:50,679 --> 00:37:51,936
he can yell at me, he can hit me.

530
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:53,320
He can do whatever he wants to me.

531
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:56,440
Just tell him to stop disappearing.

532
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,880
What the hell did you do to my brother?

533
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:05,599
You piece of shit!

534
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:08,256
He chased you all the
way to the airport that day.

535
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,280
Only to find you gone.

536
00:38:09,599 --> 00:38:10,856
He came back and got terribly sick.

537
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,920
Everywhere he went, people
would point and whisper.

538
00:38:14,039 --> 00:38:14,800
For all these years,

539
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,280
he held on to your damn promise...

540
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:18,400
that you'd be together
as long as you were alive.

541
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:20,159
And now you come back and do this to him.

542
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:22,800
How could anyone take that?

543
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:32,559
Bro.

544
00:38:37,239 --> 00:38:38,239
Xiao Chen.

545
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,880
I was always trying to
contact you from the US.

546
00:38:43,679 --> 00:38:45,000
I was always trying to find you.

547
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,400
I was too weak.

548
00:38:48,079 --> 00:38:49,239
There was nothing I could do.

549
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,320
My dad locked me in the house.

550
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:53,880
He tore up my passport.

551
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,400
I...

552
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:57,079
I couldn't go anywhere.

553
00:38:58,480 --> 00:38:59,719
I wrote you letters.

554
00:39:00,119 --> 00:39:02,159
So many of them were returned to sender.

555
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:06,960
I really thought...

556
00:39:07,519 --> 00:39:08,920
I'd never be able to come back.

557
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:12,880
I thought...

558
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:14,560
for the rest of my life...

559
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,159
I would never see you again.

560
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,400
It wasn't until my dad
arranged a marriage for me...

561
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:21,800
that I had a chance to
come back and see you.

562
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:26,640
You don't have to explain anymore.

563
00:39:27,639 --> 00:39:28,639
I forgive you.

564
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,000
Go home, Lu Feng.

565
00:39:32,153 --> 00:39:34,555
Xiao Chen... we...

566
